and move from side to side,

288
00:17:17,945 --> 00:17:20,334
from side to side,

289
00:17:20,465 --> 00:17:22,103
and he'll feel every movement.

290
00:17:22,945 --> 00:17:23,695
What's she doing?

291
00:17:23,905 --> 00:17:25,975
What the hell is she doing?

292
00:17:29,345 --> 00:17:30,380
I don't feel well...

293
00:17:31,065 --> 00:17:32,703
This isn't good...

294
00:17:32,825 --> 00:17:34,019
My blood sugar dropped.

295
00:17:34,465 --> 00:17:36,899
She's something.

296
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:38,774
Really something.

297
00:17:40,065 --> 00:17:42,454
It's a miracle, a miracle,

298
00:17:42,665 --> 00:17:44,895
he brought good luck.

299
00:17:46,225 --> 00:17:49,422
Come to Daddy.
Take off your clothes, yes. - Yes.

300
00:17:58,105 --> 00:18:00,619
I'll be the first one
who Sigi bathes.

301
00:18:00,745 --> 00:18:03,896
You wish.
I'll be there way before you.

302
00:18:04,025 --> 00:18:06,937
It won't be you, Ezra,
or you, Nick. It'll be me.

303
00:18:07,305 --> 00:18:09,057
I belong here,

304
00:18:09,545 --> 00:18:10,739
next to Rhoda.

305
00:18:10,865 --> 00:18:12,583
She's coming out,

306
00:18:12,705 --> 00:18:13,820
let's go.

307
00:18:14,745 --> 00:18:16,064
Don't let her see us.

308
00:18:16,185 --> 00:18:17,584
Have you seen my mother?

309
00:18:31,865 --> 00:18:34,459
To be or not to be,

310
00:18:35,585 --> 00:18:37,223
that is the question.

311
00:18:38,345 --> 00:18:42,861
Hamlet, you cannot escape
your destiny.

312
00:18:43,305 --> 00:18:45,182
Uncle Claudius... Murder!

313
00:18:45,545 --> 00:18:46,660
You killed my father!

314
00:18:46,985 --> 00:18:49,738
And now you have the audacity
to violate my mother?

315
00:18:49,865 --> 00:18:51,901
Come and meet thy death!

316
00:18:52,065 --> 00:18:55,137
I am your father, Hamlet.

317
00:18:55,265 --> 00:18:56,584
No!

318
00:18:57,145 --> 00:18:59,659
Fight! Fight!

319
00:19:06,705 --> 00:19:10,414
My hand! My hand!
My hand!

320
00:19:11,145 --> 00:19:13,659
Ophelia, I feel something.

321
00:19:13,985 --> 00:19:16,340
It's a strange sensation
in my belly.

322
00:19:16,585 --> 00:19:19,145
Oh, it's growing. Oh...

323
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:22,344
Tough house.
Mind you,

324
00:19:22,465 --> 00:19:25,138
half that lot out there
haven't paid for their bloody tickets.

325
00:19:26,225 --> 00:19:26,941
Go on.

326
00:19:27,985 --> 00:19:32,775
Ophelia! I'm flying!
I'm flying!

327
00:19:36,825 --> 00:19:37,780
Hello.

328
00:19:38,225 --> 00:19:41,342
Hi. This is Dorit Arbel
from Israel.

329
00:19:41,465 --> 00:19:44,821
Yes?
- Is this Lord Michael Simpson?

330
00:19:44,945 --> 00:19:46,856
This isn't a very good time.

331
00:19:46,985 --> 00:19:51,024
I'm afraid I've just opened the world
premiere of my new production,

332
00:19:51,345 --> 00:19:53,063
"Hamlet, Revenge of the Sith,"

333
00:19:53,185 --> 00:19:54,937
so thank very much.
Thank you, goodbye.

334
00:19:55,065 --> 00:19:55,895
Daniel is dead.

335
00:19:56,785 --> 00:20:01,654
Oh, I'm so sorry. Thank you for
the courtesy of letting me know.

336
00:20:02,985 --> 00:20:06,455
Excuse me, who is this Daniel? I mean,
what relation does he have to me?

337
00:20:06,625 --> 00:20:07,978
Well, he's your nephew.

338
00:20:08,385 --> 00:20:09,613
The son of Rhoda.

339
00:20:10,705 --> 00:20:11,854
Oh, dear.

340
00:20:12,385 --> 00:20:14,535
Lord Simpson,
we know you're in there.

341
00:20:14,705 --> 00:20:18,141
If you don't open the door, Dennis here
is gonna have to break your knees.

342
00:20:19,865 --> 00:20:21,742
You don't have the rights
for the play.

343
00:20:21,865 --> 00:20:24,095
What are you thinking of doing,
jumping out of the window?

344
00:20:24,265 --> 00:20:26,984
We're gonna shove one of these
light-swords up your ass!

345
00:20:27,945 --> 00:20:30,061
You're gonna pay me
every penny!

346
00:20:30,185 --> 00:20:35,020
I have to leave now. Will you give
my condolences to my sister?

347
00:20:35,145 --> 00:20:37,613
She doesn't know.
She's in a coma.

348
00:20:37,745 --> 00:20:39,463
Rhoda? In a coma?

349
00:20:39,585 --> 00:20:40,938
Well, I thought you knew that.

350
00:20:41,065 --> 00:20:43,260
Now that Daniel is dead
we don't have a lot of money.

351
00:20:43,425 --> 00:20:45,780
We need a short-term loan for...
- What about Rhoda's money?

352
00:20:46,105 --> 00:20:47,538
The big place in Jerusalem?

353
00:20:47,665 --> 00:20:49,223
Eliyahu will not give us money.

354
00:20:49,425 --> 00:20:50,904
You're damned right he won't.

355
00:20:51,025 --> 00:20:53,141
Now, that is my family's property

356
00:20:53,305 --> 00:20:55,614
and my father, I can assure you,

357
00:20:55,745 --> 00:20:58,862
had no intention of it falling into
the hands of a Jewish terrorist!

358
00:20:58,985 --> 00:21:00,100
Well, he's not a terrorist.

359
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:03,861
One may stop being a terrorist.
One can scarcely cease being a Jew.

360
00:21:04,745 --> 00:21:07,418
We just need a little loan.
It's a small thing.

361
00:21:08,185 --> 00:21:10,062
You're one of the richest families
in England.

362
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:12,653
Oh, yes, somewhere between
the Queen and Victoria Beckham.

363
00:21:12,785 --> 00:21:17,939
The Simpson family made
their considerable fortune out of tea.

364
00:21:18,065 --> 00:21:20,738
The father of Rhoda and Michael
served in India

365
00:21:20,865 --> 00:21:23,254
and then in the Mandatory Police
in Palestine.

366
00:21:23,745 --> 00:21:26,384
He was a hunter and a boxer.

367
00:21:26,945 --> 00:21:29,698
Now, the father was bitterly
disappointed with his children,

368
00:21:30,025 --> 00:21:33,540
so when Michael became
a theatre actor

369
00:21:33,905 --> 00:21:36,339
his father decided,
in retaliation,

370
00:21:36,705 --> 00:21:40,095
to donate the entire
family fortune to science,

371
00:21:40,305 --> 00:21:42,978
leaving Michael with
practically nothing.

372
00:21:53,345 --> 00:21:54,539
How's it going, buddy?

373
00:21:56,425 --> 00:21:57,744
I'm fine.

374
00:21:58,625 --> 00:21:59,944
What are you doing here?

375
00:22:01,265 --> 00:22:02,459
My mom isn't home.

376
00:22:03,785 --> 00:22:06,982
Hello, Dedi.
- Hello, Dorit.

377
00:22:07,345 --> 00:22:08,334
You little scamp...

378
00:22:09,185 --> 00:22:09,981
I like that.

379
00:22:13,305 --> 00:22:14,101
Dorit,

380
00:22:15,305 --> 00:22:18,024
I might have a lead for you,

381
00:22:18,145 --> 00:22:19,180
I've been thinking
about you all day,

382
00:22:19,305 --> 00:22:23,139
and I might have
a solution for your problem.

383
00:22:23,425 --> 00:22:25,302
I found a monetary fund

384
00:22:25,465 --> 00:22:27,933
that can give you
a short-term loan.

385
00:22:28,825 --> 00:22:29,575
Here, take it.

386
00:22:29,705 --> 00:22:31,582
We don't need handouts.
- Stop it, Jonathan.

387
00:22:32,305 --> 00:22:33,021
Thank you.

388
00:22:33,145 --> 00:22:35,864
I can get you this amount
every month.

389
00:22:36,025 --> 00:22:37,458
It's not much,
I really liked Daniel.

390
00:22:37,585 --> 00:22:41,294
No one at the bank knows about this.
I'm bending the rules.

391
00:22:41,425 --> 00:22:42,653
I bought you a computer game,

392
00:22:44,025 --> 00:22:46,585
"Car Thief,"
but school comes first, right?

393
00:22:46,705 --> 00:22:47,421
Do you need a ride?

394
00:22:47,545 --> 00:22:50,059
I can take you to work,
and you to school. - No need. - Sure.

395
00:22:50,865 --> 00:22:51,775
Yes.

396
00:23:28,385 --> 00:23:30,853
You can exchange the game
if you like.

397
00:23:32,225 --> 00:23:34,819
It says so in the fine print.
Here, see?

398
00:23:34,945 --> 00:23:37,015
You have up to a month.

399
00:23:38,905 --> 00:23:41,294
God is in the fine print, Jonathan.

400
00:23:53,465 --> 00:23:54,614
Come on, Jonathan.

401
00:24:28,145 --> 00:24:30,056
Hey, kid...

402
00:24:31,825 --> 00:24:33,702
Hey, moron.

403
00:24:34,945 --> 00:24:36,219
Are you playing?

404
00:24:40,345 --> 00:24:43,098
I'm getting some tea,
then I'll be back to slaughter you.

405
00:24:47,705 --> 00:24:49,058
Let him win.

406
00:24:49,905 --> 00:24:52,021
Why? I'll finish him off
in five moves.

407
00:24:52,145 --> 00:24:55,899
Let him win, listen to me,
I know him.

408
00:24:56,065 --> 00:24:56,975
What were you talking about?

409
00:24:57,185 --> 00:24:59,415
I asked if he has a girlfriend.

410
00:25:00,145 --> 00:25:04,616
Well, sonny-boy? Has anyone
let you touch her cherries yet?

411
00:25:05,865 --> 00:25:09,062
I met your grandmother
at the Bank of Palestine

412
00:25:09,385 --> 00:25:10,864
in Jerusalem.

413
00:25:12,625 --> 00:25:14,581
She had a summer job there

414
00:25:15,025 --> 00:25:17,255
and I came in holding a gun.

415
00:25:18,585 --> 00:25:22,419
There she was, the prettiest girl
in the world, 17 years old.

416
00:25:22,665 --> 00:25:26,419
The daughter
of the British Chief of Police.

417
00:25:27,385 --> 00:25:29,421
I looked into her eyes and said:

418
00:25:29,545 --> 00:25:33,584
A girl like you needs a man that will
look at her beauty all her life.

419
00:25:34,065 --> 00:25:35,293
This is my address.

420
00:25:35,745 --> 00:25:38,134
Come to me
if you are looking for true love.

421
00:25:38,265 --> 00:25:39,664
You walked in holding a gun?

422
00:25:39,785 --> 00:25:40,900
I had a machine gun.

423
00:25:41,025 --> 00:25:42,378
Were you bank robbers?

424
00:25:43,505 --> 00:25:44,824
You and Nick?

425
00:25:45,625 --> 00:25:47,741
We did it for the Jewish people.

426
00:25:48,465 --> 00:25:50,501
We did it for the girls.

427
00:25:51,745 --> 00:25:54,817
Where did you get guns?
- It's still confidential.

428
00:25:54,985 --> 00:25:55,974
Tell me, sonny,

429
00:25:56,505 --> 00:26:00,339
who's that girl you like?
- She's in my class.

430
00:26:00,785 --> 00:26:02,901
Is she pretty?
- I don't know,

431
00:26:03,065 --> 00:26:04,942
I don't have the authority
to determine that.

432
00:26:05,105 --> 00:26:07,744
Listen, kid,
all that counts is getting laid.

433
00:26:08,185 --> 00:26:09,937
If a girl says yes, go for it,

434
00:26:10,105 --> 00:26:11,618
don't make my mistake,

435
00:26:11,865 --> 00:26:14,902
a neighbor once babysat me
and I said no.

436
00:26:15,265 --> 00:26:17,017
I waited ten years after that

437
00:26:17,185 --> 00:26:20,018
and I ended up
going to a whore downtown.

438
00:26:20,145 --> 00:26:21,134
Shut up, Nick.

439
00:26:21,265 --> 00:26:25,144
Life begins the first time
a girl gives it to you

440
00:26:25,385 --> 00:26:27,899
and it ends the last time
you get it.

441
00:26:28,025 --> 00:26:30,334
Go to that girl tomorrow
and tell her:

442
00:26:30,465 --> 00:26:33,423
Let's not waste time,
life is short.

443
00:26:33,545 --> 00:26:36,105
I may love you now,
but it might not last.

444
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:37,937
Here's my number,

445
00:26:38,065 --> 00:26:40,738
call me if you're looking
for true love.

446
00:26:41,345 --> 00:26:43,256
Grandpa, I can't tell her that,

447
00:26:43,545 --> 00:26:44,500
