will laugh at me.

448
00:26:44,625 --> 00:26:48,413
Your generation sees
so much sex and ass,

449
00:26:48,585 --> 00:26:50,223
but you have no concept
of simple love.

450
00:26:51,625 --> 00:26:54,093
Say goodbye to your queen, kid.

451
00:26:57,345 --> 00:26:58,903
Your end is near.

452
00:26:59,185 --> 00:27:00,982
You're not bad for a kid.

453
00:27:01,145 --> 00:27:03,056
You definitely inherited my skill.

454
00:27:03,345 --> 00:27:04,116
Checkmate.

455
00:27:04,745 --> 00:27:06,463
You can't go here
because of the rook

456
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:08,820
and you can't go here...
- I know what checkmate is.

457
00:27:10,105 --> 00:27:11,174
It's one of Kasparov's tricks,

458
00:27:11,825 --> 00:27:14,703
you have to know
when to sacrifice your queen.

459
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:17,256
When I got up for tea
did he move the pieces?

460
00:27:18,065 --> 00:27:19,544
I didn't cheat, I never do.

461
00:27:19,665 --> 00:27:21,815
You're stupid.
I'd cheat if I could.

462
00:27:21,985 --> 00:27:22,815
No, you wouldn't.

463
00:27:22,945 --> 00:27:23,661
Yes, he would.

464
00:27:23,785 --> 00:27:25,264
Everyone cheats
when it's convenient.

465
00:27:25,705 --> 00:27:27,297
What did your stupid father teach you?

466
00:27:27,425 --> 00:27:28,778
My father was smarter than you.

467
00:27:29,665 --> 00:27:30,575
You didn't know him.

468
00:27:30,705 --> 00:27:33,458
Listen, halfwit, he was my son
before he was your father.

469
00:27:33,585 --> 00:27:34,859
He was an honest man,

470
00:27:34,985 --> 00:27:37,545
which you'll never be.

471
00:27:38,905 --> 00:27:40,304
Why do you come here?

472
00:27:40,665 --> 00:27:43,225
Why don't you have
any friends?

473
00:27:43,385 --> 00:27:45,535
Eliyahu, for God's sake,
leave the kid alone.

474
00:27:45,825 --> 00:27:47,543
I understand
why Dad never spoke to you.

475
00:27:48,145 --> 00:27:50,101
You're a liar, a cheat
and a psychopath.

476
00:27:50,265 --> 00:27:51,857
You don't know
nothing about nothing.

477
00:27:52,505 --> 00:27:54,063
It's my dad's chessboard!

478
00:27:54,185 --> 00:27:56,062
I bought it for him, idiot.

479
00:27:56,185 --> 00:27:58,699
How can you possibly
treat people like this?

480
00:27:58,825 --> 00:28:01,020
One flies 3,000 miles

481
00:28:01,145 --> 00:28:02,897
to find one's beloved sister

482
00:28:03,025 --> 00:28:05,016
in the worst corner
of this dump.

483
00:28:05,705 --> 00:28:07,696
I'm terribly sorry, Mr. Simpson...

484
00:28:07,825 --> 00:28:08,894
Lord Simpson!

485
00:28:09,545 --> 00:28:11,456
One's great-great-great-grandfather

486
00:28:11,585 --> 00:28:15,339
did not kill the Teutonic king
with his bare hands 800 years ago,

487
00:28:15,465 --> 00:28:18,059
for his descendants
to become plain "Mr." again.

488
00:28:18,185 --> 00:28:21,302
What rock did that snake
crawl out from under?

489
00:28:21,425 --> 00:28:22,904
I'm sorry, Lord Simpson.

490
00:28:23,265 --> 00:28:25,381
Rhoda is getting
the best treatment,

491
