01:17:41,905 --> 01:17:44,624
Do you want him to see you
with another man? - Stop it!

1288
01:17:45,785 --> 01:17:47,616
So what if
you're smarter than me?

1289
01:17:48,065 --> 01:17:51,182
So what if you have
a smart-ass answer to everything?

1290
01:17:52,025 --> 01:17:53,458
You think it's easy for me?

1291
01:17:53,665 --> 01:17:55,576
That I don't feel terrible about it?

1292
01:17:56,825 --> 01:17:59,385
But how long do I have to wait?

1293
01:18:00,785 --> 01:18:02,184
I loved your father,

1294
01:18:03,825 --> 01:18:06,976
but a 40-year-old woman can't
move to an old-age home and die.

1295
01:18:38,825 --> 01:18:39,621
Nick,

1296
01:18:40,385 --> 01:18:43,536
remember, "only death can
release us from the ranks."

1297
01:18:47,745 --> 01:18:52,102
Yalla, Yalla!
Let's go and hunt those elephants!

1298
01:18:55,025 --> 01:18:56,458
Mr. Gurevitch,
please come with me.

1299
01:19:03,825 --> 01:19:05,463
Don't forget to break
the security camera.

1300
01:19:05,585 --> 01:19:07,701
Are you crazy?
Break the camera? Never.

1301
01:19:08,985 --> 01:19:12,216
Simona!
I'm ready for my close-up.

1302
01:19:19,865 --> 01:19:22,618
It's such an honor
to have you here, Lord Simpson.

1303
01:19:23,545 --> 01:19:27,174
Your money's here,
two million Euros, in the safe.

1304
01:19:27,465 --> 01:19:30,298
You can call me Alfred.
It's a kind of nickname.

1305
01:19:34,265 --> 01:19:35,095
Jonathan...

1306
01:19:36,745 --> 01:19:37,939
Dedi.

1307
01:19:38,265 --> 01:19:41,462
Good afternoon. - Hello!
Good afternoon, Mr. Simpson.

1308
01:19:41,585 --> 01:19:45,214
Lord Simpson.
- Oh, sorry. Please have a seat.

1309
01:19:46,705 --> 01:19:49,697
Okay then, you want
your two million Euros. - Yes.

1310
01:19:50,465 --> 01:19:54,697
Small denominations, used.
Unmarked.

1311
01:20:07,305 --> 01:20:10,342
Do you have a guarantee?
- I'm a walking guarantee.

1312
01:20:15,625 --> 01:20:17,377
Such a great humor.

1313
01:20:26,745 --> 01:20:31,261
It's a stick-up!
It's a stick-up!

1314
01:20:31,745 --> 01:20:33,383
Good, Nick, good...

1315
01:20:39,425 --> 01:20:41,620
Who set off the alarm?

1316
01:20:41,745 --> 01:20:42,973
Disable it now.

1317
01:20:43,105 --> 01:20:44,424
Tell the police to forget it.

1318
01:20:45,705 --> 01:20:47,343
I'm sorry, you have to leave.

1319
01:20:49,505 --> 01:20:51,257
I was just kidding, I...

1320
01:20:51,665 --> 01:20:53,144
I'm here to deposit money.

1321
01:20:53,745 --> 01:20:56,384
Then sit here and don't
make trouble, okay? - Okay.

1322
01:20:56,545 --> 01:20:57,500
Good.

1323
01:20:58,785 --> 01:20:59,774
Hold these.

1324
01:21:01,465 --> 01:21:02,580
Put them on me.

1325
01:21:05,065 --> 01:21:06,054
Good.

1326
01:21:09,705 --> 01:21:10,899
Do you need the restroom?

1327
01:21:11,065 --> 01:21:14,341
No, I'm using a mobile.

1328
01:21:15,425 --> 01:21:17,416
Nick, you can't stand here.
Go sit down.

1329
01:21:17,545 --> 01:21:19,422
I want to stand there.
What'll you do to me?

1330
01:21:19,545 --> 01:21:22,218
That door must stay open,
it's the security room.

1331
01:21:22,345 --> 01:21:24,700
Nick, do as I say
or you're out.

1332
01:21:25,385 --> 01:21:26,156
What's the big deal?

1333
01:21:26,185 --> 01:21:27,777
Do I look 5 years old to you?

1334
01:21:27,945 --> 01:21:29,458
Nick, with all due respect,

1335
01:21:29,585 --> 01:21:32,099
go sit over there, you hear me?

1336
01:21:34,105 --> 01:21:36,061
And what if I don't?

1337
01:21:37,265 --> 01:21:38,778
What'll you do to me?

1338
01:21:40,105 --> 01:21:41,424
What'll you do to me?

1339
01:21:42,145 --> 01:21:43,419
What'll you do to me?

1340
01:21:43,585 --> 01:21:44,356
Nick.

1341
01:21:45,131 --> 01:21:46,564
Nick, what are you doing?
- Is he crazy?

1342
01:21:46,691 --> 01:21:49,330
Now I want to stand here.
What'll you do?

1343
01:21:49,451 --> 01:21:51,009
He's supposed to be a hostage.

1344
01:21:51,131 --> 01:21:53,122
What'll you do now?

1345
01:21:53,451 --> 01:21:55,442
I want to stand here.
What'll you do?

1346
01:21:55,731 --> 01:21:56,447
Nick...

1347
01:21:56,571 --> 01:21:57,321
Don't move.

1348
01:21:57,451 --> 01:21:58,520
Put down the gun,

1349
01:21:58,651 --> 01:22:00,289
Nick, you hear me?

1350
01:22:02,371 --> 01:22:04,009
Put down the gun.

1351
01:22:05,211 --> 01:22:06,280
Shit...

1352
01:22:07,891 --> 01:22:09,529
Things are out of control.

1353
01:22:11,571 --> 01:22:14,643
I took the security guard's gun.

1354
01:22:15,211 --> 01:22:18,123
Damn it...
This is a stick-up!

1355
01:22:18,811 --> 01:22:19,960
This is a stick-up!

1356
01:22:20,251 --> 01:22:22,367
Get down, you,
this is a stick-up!

1357
01:22:22,651 --> 01:22:23,879
Nick, Nick, are you robbing me?

1358
01:22:24,091 --> 01:22:25,604
You're our client.

1359
01:22:25,771 --> 01:22:26,760
Are you surprised?

1360
01:22:26,891 --> 01:22:28,961
You should've read
the fine print.

1361
01:22:29,251 --> 01:22:32,288
And what happens to people
who can't read the fine print?

1362
01:22:33,811 --> 01:22:35,039
Don't move.

1363
01:22:35,571 --> 01:22:37,004
Nobody move!

1364
01:22:40,491 --> 01:22:41,924
Everyone calm down.

1365
01:22:42,211 --> 01:22:43,405
Lie down on the floor.

1366
01:22:43,651 --> 01:22:46,165
The floor's clean.
It's just been washed,

1367
01:22:46,331 --> 01:22:48,765
we're insured, don't worry
about the stick-up.

1368
01:22:49,051 --> 01:22:53,169
Everybody!
I have a monologue!

1369
01:22:53,331 --> 01:22:57,609
Oh, evil, I listen carefully...

1370
01:22:57,851 --> 01:22:58,966
What's he doing, Grandpa?

1371
01:22:59,731 --> 01:23:02,165
He wanted a monologue.
Like an idiot, I listened to you.

1372
01:23:02,331 --> 01:23:06,768
...in times of war
parts played may alter,

1373
01:23:06,891 --> 01:23:10,725
the kidnapper sometimes
becomes the prisoner!

1374
01:23:11,451 --> 01:23:13,442
Son of a bitch,
what is he doing?

1375
01:23:13,571 --> 01:23:15,687
Grandpa, I think
he's trying to say something.

1376
01:23:16,011 --> 01:23:17,569
Simona!
- I'm coming!

1377
01:23:17,691 --> 01:23:18,806
Nick will kidnap us...

1378
01:23:19,211 --> 01:23:22,362
we'll stick to the plan,
it'll work.

1379
01:23:22,491 --> 01:23:24,129
Stop crying!
- I can't.

1380
01:23:24,251 --> 01:23:25,445
Stop crying, look presentable.

1381
01:23:25,571 --> 01:23:27,846
Everyone, look presentable,
this is a bank.

1382
01:23:31,331 --> 01:23:33,401
Don't hurt us!

1383
01:23:33,531 --> 01:23:36,409
Lie down, old man,
on the floor.

1384
01:23:36,571 --> 01:23:38,209
Jonathan,
what are you doing here?

1385
01:23:38,531 --> 01:23:39,441
Lie down.

1386
01:23:40,091 --> 01:23:42,446
Kid, come to the safe with me.

1387
01:23:42,571 --> 01:23:43,799
You, Hamlet, too.

1388
01:23:46,771 --> 01:23:48,170
Don't move, don't move!

1389
01:23:53,251 --> 01:23:55,446
The security guard's gun is loaded.
Don't hurt the boy.

1390
01:23:55,571 --> 01:23:58,324
Don't hurt him,
he has a wonderful mother.

1391
01:23:58,531 --> 01:23:59,759
The safe.

1392
01:24:00,731 --> 01:24:03,609
Don't move. - Lie down, old man.
- Don't move.

1393
01:24:09,091 --> 01:24:10,649
I don't know
what came over me.

1394
01:24:11,051 --> 01:24:13,360
Suddenly, I was holding a gun.

1395
01:24:15,571 --> 01:24:18,608
Continue as planned.
Tell us to open the safe.

1396
01:24:18,891 --> 01:24:20,370
Open the safe, kid.

1397
01:24:20,931 --> 01:24:21,647
Thank you.

1398
01:24:25,371 --> 01:24:26,850
Move it!

1399
01:24:28,251 --> 01:24:29,366
You too!

1400
01:24:35,691 --> 01:24:36,646
It was...

1401
01:24:52,411 --> 01:24:55,687
What's wrong with this?
- It's mechanical, just turn it.

1402
01:24:58,211 --> 01:25:00,361
Let me help you.
- Yes.

1403
01:25:01,251 --> 01:25:02,366
Hold it, please.

1404
01:25:09,051 --> 01:25:11,804
Nick, we have to hurry.
The cops will be here soon.

1405
01:25:11,931 --> 01:25:15,685
Don't do anything!
This is a hostage situation!

1406
01:25:15,811 --> 01:25:17,039
He has a bomb!

1407
01:25:17,811 --> 01:25:19,403
Allah Akbar!

1408
01:25:19,771 --> 01:25:21,363
Allah Akbar!

1409
01:25:23,051 --> 01:25:24,245
No!

1410
01:25:31,771 --> 01:25:32,681
What did I do?

1411
01:25:33,931 --> 01:25:35,444
You don't know who I am!

1412
01:25:35,571 --> 01:25:37,084
You don't know...
- Stop it!

1413
01:25:38,331 --> 01:25:39,320
Idiot!

1414
01:25:39,491 --> 01:25:40,207
Jonathan...

1415
01:25:40,811 --> 01:25:43,120
It's all right, Jonathan,
it's all right.

1416
01:25:43,251 --> 01:25:44,240
Vlada, enough.

1417
01:25:44,411 --> 01:25:46,447
Lord Simpson, I'm so sorry.
It's all under control now.

1418
01:25:46,571 --> 01:25:47,765
That's perfectly all right.

1419
01:25:47,891 --> 01:25:50,280
Excuse me. Excuse me!

1420
01:25:50,531 --> 01:25:52,249
I believe this is yours.

1421
01:25:57,011 --> 01:26:01,801
Simona... I have been
so worried about you.

1422
01:26:01,931 --> 01:26:04,809
Are you all right? - It was horrible.
- Yes, of course.

1423
01:26:04,931 --> 01:26:06,250
There, there, there...

1424
01:26:06,371 --> 01:26:07,804
I'm sure
everything will be well.

1425
01:26:07,931 --> 01:26:10,764
I have to be somewhere now.
Excuse me.

1426
01:26:10,891 --> 01:26:12,961
Oh, would you get my umbrella
and my hat?

1427
01:26:18,931 --> 01:26:21,570
Go home and keep quiet.

1428
01:26:22,291 --> 01:26:25,408
They'll keep Nick here
in the senile ward.

1429
01:26:25,611 --> 01:26:26,930
Nobody knows
you were involved.

1430
01:26:27,051 --> 01:26:28,609
You'll be fine
if you keep your mouth shut.

1431
01:26:29,211 --> 01:26:30,041
Grandpa,

1432
01:26:31,451 --> 01:26:33,362
my mom wants us
to move in with Dedi.

1433
01:26:34,731 --> 01:26:36,687
It's... far away.

1434
01:26:38,531 --> 01:26:40,362
I won't be able to see you
every day.

1435
01:26:42,291 --> 01:26:43,406
That's great.

1436
01:26:44,731 --> 01:26:46,449
Dedi has money.

1437
01:26:46,931 --> 01:26:49,081
You'll go to a school for the gifted
like you always wanted.

1438
01:26:49,811 --> 01:26:51,403
I don't really want to.

1439
01:26:51,651 --> 01:26:54,484
Why not? You cried like a baby
that you wanted to.

1440
01:26:55,211 --> 01:26:57,202
I want to be with you.
- What for?

1441
01:26:57,971 --> 01:27:01,122
What do you want with some old men
who have 5 minutes left to live?

1442
01:27:02,331 --> 01:27:04,401
I'd be glad
if you stopped coming.

1443
01:27:04,731 --> 01:27:05,502
Grandpa,

1444
01:27:05,771 --> 01:27:07,443
don't do this to me, not now.

1445
01:27:07,771 --> 01:27:09,966
I know you're not like this.

1446
01:27:10,291 --> 01:27:13,442
Don't tell me what I'm like.
What do you know? Spoiled brat...

1447
01:27:14,011 --> 01:27:16,127
You can't go to school
without getting beaten up.

1448
01:27:16,291 --> 01:27:17,804
You're pissed that we blew it.

1449
01:27:17,971 --> 01:27:19,120
That you're too old
to rob a bank,

1450
01:27:19,251 --> 01:27:21,242
that you're useless old fogies.

1451
01:27:21,651 --> 01:27:23,050
I'm too old?

1452
01:27:24,291 --> 01:27:26,646
We blew it because of
your stupid plan.

1453
01:27:26,771 --> 01:27:28,409
Listen, you loser,

1454
01:27:28,531 --> 01:27:31,170
you and your wimpy
English genes,

1455
01:27:31,411 --> 01:27:32,730
you're a loser
just like your dad.

1456
01:27:32,851 --> 01:27:35,365
I won't let you argue with me
like you did with Dad.

1457
01:27:35,651 --> 01:27:36,606
What did I do to him?

1458
01:27:38,331 --> 01:27:40,606
You left him at a movie
and went to see another woman.

1459
01:27:40,731 --> 01:27:42,084
He wasn't supposed to see that.

1460
01:27:44,171 --> 01:27:46,162
That dimwit was supposed
to watch the movie.

1461
01:27:47,611 --> 01:27:49,408
But he couldn't stand
being alone for 5 minutes.

1462
01:27:49,531 --> 01:27:51,089
I don't get it,
you love Grandma.

1463
01:27:51,331 --> 01:27:52,730
Nobody loves anyone so much

1464
01:27:52,851 --> 01:27:54,887
that they don't want to sleep
with another woman.

1465
01:27:57,291 --> 01:27:58,963
You wanted them
to have an abortion.

1466
01:27:59,771 --> 01:28:01,409
You didn't want me.

1467
01:28:01,531 --> 01:28:04,170
Your mother got pregnant
and had my son by the balls.

1468
01:28:04,691 --> 01:28:06,602
He should've done better,
he was a genius

1469
01:28:07,251 --> 01:28:08,604
but he threw it all away.

1470
01:28:09,331 --> 01:28:11,003
A security guard at a bank.

1471
01:28:12,291 --> 01:28:13,485
Who cares about your troubles?

1472
01:28:13,651 --> 01:28:14,561
Do I owe you anything?

1473
01:28:14,891 --> 01:28:17,200
Your mother's spreading her legs
for your sake.

1474
01:28:17,731 --> 01:28:19,722
Maybe she isn't as crazy
as we thought.

1475
01:28:19,851 --> 01:28:20,761
Go buy her some flowers.

1476
01:28:21,091 --> 01:28:22,444
Get out of my sight.

1477
01:29:13,411 --> 01:29:14,605
Nick.

1478
01:29:15,011 --> 01:29:15,887
Nick.

1479
01:29:16,851 --> 01:29:20,764
Jonathan, sonny-boy,
good to see you.

1480
01:29:22,651 --> 01:29:24,960
Was there anything
on the news?

1481
01:29:28,211 --> 01:29:29,530
Where's Grandpa?

1482
01:29:33,091 --> 01:29:34,604
Nick, where's Grandpa?

1483
01:29:36,371 --> 01:29:40,205
He went to rob the bank,
like in the good old days.

1484
01:29:45,451 --> 01:29:48,204
You walk in with a gun,
fire into the air and yell:

1485
01:29:48,691 --> 01:29:51,330
"A free country for a free people! "
- No!

1486
01:29:51,691 --> 01:29:53,329
No, they'll kill him,

1487
01:29:53,691 --> 01:29:54,726
they'll be waiting for him.

1488
01:29:56,091 --> 01:29:58,207
Eliyahu thought of everything,

1489
01:29:58,331 --> 01:30:00,799
he took out life insurance
30 years ago

1490
01:30:01,011 --> 01:30:04,242
and now he listed you as beneficiary
instead of Rhoda.

1491
01:30:04,571 --> 01:30:08,849
If anything happens, God forbid,
it's all yours.

1492
01:30:19,771 --> 01:30:20,806
Jonathan!

1493
01:30:21,371 --> 01:30:23,327
Hello. Dedi's busy,
he can't see you now.

1494
01:30:28,091 --> 01:30:29,410
What is this?

1495
01:30:30,691 --> 01:30:32,568
Another stick-up?
Twice in a week?

1496
01:30:33,211 --> 01:30:34,883
I'm changing mezuzahs,
what are you doing?

1497
01:30:35,211 --> 01:30:37,247
Eliyahu came into my room,
broke my nose,

1498
01:30:37,611 --> 01:30:39,010
and said, "That's for Dorit."

1499
01:30:40,411 --> 01:30:44,927
Then he smashed
my top row of teeth,

1500
01:30:45,051 --> 01:30:46,279
60,000 shekels' worth.

1501
01:30:46,931 --> 01:30:49,923
He said,
"That's so you'll open the safe."

1502
01:30:51,491 --> 01:30:52,526
What did you do?

1503
01:30:53,211 --> 01:30:54,644
I opened the safe.

1504
01:30:56,971 --> 01:30:59,439
I sued the bank.
I received no damages, no pension.

1505
01:31:01,011 --> 01:31:02,683
I tripped up on the fine print.

1506
01:31:03,811 --> 01:31:05,039
I have a gun here,

1507
01:31:05,211 --> 01:31:07,566
nobody moves or I'll shoot!

1508
01:31:09,251 --> 01:31:11,970
I have a gas can here,
I'll burn the bank down!

1509
01:31:13,571 --> 01:31:15,721
Good thing you're here.
Give me the bag.

1510
01:31:20,971 --> 01:31:21,960
The cameras aren't working,

1511
01:31:22,291 --> 01:31:24,851
nobody will know
you came in or went out.

1512
01:31:28,411 --> 01:31:29,446
Put it in.

1513
01:31:34,291 --> 01:31:35,644
I'll help you up.

1514
01:31:37,011 --> 01:31:38,603
I'm staying here,

1515
01:31:39,171 --> 01:31:41,526
Don't worry, those shitheads
won't take me alive.

1516
01:31:42,051 --> 01:31:43,279
Like Kasparov,

1517
01:31:43,651 --> 01:31:46,245
sometimes you sacrifice the king
if you want to win.

1518
01:31:47,171 --> 01:31:48,809
But...

1519
01:31:48,931 --> 01:31:50,364
I don't want you
to die because of me.

1520
01:31:50,491 --> 01:31:51,719
It's enough I killed Dad.

1521
01:31:52,451 --> 01:31:55,090
Shh, kid.
Nobody died because of you.

1522
01:31:55,451 --> 01:31:58,568
I can see you, shitheads!
Don't move or I'll shoot!

1523
01:31:59,771 --> 01:32:01,523
Kids and old people
are transparent.

1524
01:32:02,251 --> 01:32:04,924
Walk out slowly and whistle.

1525
01:32:05,051 --> 01:32:06,370
You're coming with me.

1526
01:32:07,091 --> 01:32:10,003
All my life
I never did anything right,

1527
01:32:10,531 --> 01:32:13,125
not as a father,
not as a husband.

1528
01:32:13,851 --> 01:32:18,606
I didn't even have the guts
to kill Rhoda when I should have.

1529
01:32:19,331 --> 01:32:24,883
Now I have a chance
to be a grandfather,

1530
01:32:25,491 --> 01:32:27,004
your grandfather.

1531
01:32:28,531 --> 01:32:30,567
Take the money, Jonathan,

1532
01:32:30,691 --> 01:32:33,683
go, go, my boy, go.

1533
01:32:39,811 --> 01:32:42,166
Go, it's okay. Go.

1534
01:32:42,931 --> 01:32:44,967
Go, run.

1535
01:32:45,851 --> 01:32:48,160
Run! Go! Go!

1536
01:33:11,331 --> 01:33:14,721
